  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_133142791" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/133142791" />
    <a title="Lynn" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/422624-lynn"><img alt="Lynn" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1190938741p2/422624.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/133142791?book_show_action=true">Dec 01, 2010</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Lynn" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Lynn" href="/user/show/422624-lynn">Lynn</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer133142791" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17582423487049693823">I know most of this stuff already, but Reich says it all so well. <br/><br/>Slim book about where we are really at and why - not the usual whining about those greedy financial people, though of course they are mentioned. The long-term problem in the US is really due to the wealth gap and the demise of the working and middle class. <br/><br/>My dad, not an economist, explained to me that this was why the Depression lasted so long - because most people could not afford to buy stuff which kept money out of circulation</span>
  <span id="freeText17582423487049693823" style="display:none">I know most of this stuff already, but Reich says it all so well. <br /><br />Slim book about where we are really at and why - not the usual whining about those greedy financial people, though of course they are mentioned. The long-term problem in the US is really due to the wealth gap and the demise of the working and middle class. <br /><br />My dad, not an economist, explained to me that this was why the Depression lasted so long - because most people could not afford to buy stuff which kept money out of circulation, perpetuating the downward spiral until government transferred money to them through the programs and ultimately the war. Reich says the long term problems are not going to get fixed until we have reforms that bring back more income equality, and he writes about the impending fascism that is gaining momentum. He tries to be more upbeat about the possibility of reform than other commentators I have heard recently, but that is the least convincing part of this presentation.</span>
  <a data-text-id="17582423487049693823" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

