          <div class="stacked" tyle="padding-bottom:15px">
            <span class="readable">&ldquo;The problem was not that Americans spent beyond their means but that their means had not kept up with what the larger economy could and should have been able to provide them. the American economy had been growing briskly, and America's middle class naturally expected to share in that growth. But it didn't. A larger and larger portion of the economy's winnings had gone to people at the top.&rdquo;</span>
